cassia.util.parallel

Class ConcatenatedList<T>

  • AbstractContainer<T>
    • AbstractCollection<T>
      • cassia.util.parallel.ConcatenatedList<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Collection<T>, Container<T>, Fun_0_1 <Long,T>, Indexed<T>, Iterable<T>, List<T>, Settable<Long,T>, Any

    public class ConcatenatedList<T>
extends AbstractCollection<T>
implements List<T>
    An implementation of List to concatenate multiple lists. It only remembers the references to the input lists. The toArrayList() method generates a concatenated result as an ArrayList instance.
